1053
01:13:33,930 --> 01:13:34,251
Scott: Right.

1054
01:13:34,392 --> 01:13:41,090
Scott: It doesn't have a lot of controls on it because you're at the Apple TV interfaces was taking care of the complexity as opposed to lots of buttons.

1055
01:13:41,370 --> 01:13:55,590
Rym: But now you have the situation where the user experience of the TV itself and how it portrays those menus can become a problem, especially now because you have a remote control where the only buttons you're actually using are the arrows and the enter and the back.

1056
01:13:56,051 --> 01:14:04,510
Rym: And yet they still tend to have a lot of other buttons that often aren't that useful because they don't actually do anything for most users, which makes them confusing.

1057
01:14:05,032 --> 01:14:09,570
Rym: And a lot of non-technical people just give up and just have broken AV systems.

1058
01:14:10,190 --> 01:14:17,710
Scott: Well, I think, you know, there are some things we've seen that remote control has been added to recently, like thermostats, relatively recent remote control thermostats.

1059
01:14:19,012 --> 01:14:28,710
